  "bio": "<p>Dewone was born healthy and joyful. But as a toddler, he faced something unimaginable. A severe burn injury led to bacterial meningitis, and one heartbreaking day, he was found unresponsive and went without oxygen for over an hour. The stroke that followed changed his life. Dewone lost his ability to speak, was diagnosed with epilepsy and cerebral palsy, and now needs full-time care every day.</p><p>But even after all of this, his spirit stayed strong. Dewone brings joy wherever he goes. His smile is contagious, his affection is real, and his love for movement—tossing balls, playing with light-up toys, and interacting with strings and objects—shows everyone what true happiness looks like. His amazing mother, Jade, has supported him through every moment, living by her motto:&nbsp;\"Take care of what you pray for.\"&nbsp;Her devotion is truly remarkable.</p><p>But devotion alone couldn’t make their bathroom safe. To bathe Dewone, Jade had to lift him every day, which was exhausting and risky. Without padded walls or the right setup, his safety was always at risk. Something needed to change.That’s when we stepped in to help.</p><p>Thanks to the generous support of&nbsp;Jackson Healthcare, a long-time&nbsp;partner in our mission to help Atlanta’s special needs children and their families, Sunshine on a Ranney Day renovated Dewone’s bathroom and bedroom. Now, these spaces finally work&nbsp;for&nbsp;both him and Jade.</p><p>The new walk-in shower lets Jade bathe Dewone without having to lift him. Padded walls help keep him safe as he works on his mobility. And in a detail that always makes us smile,&nbsp;Mike Kamber and the Therapy Gyms&nbsp;team didn’t just install the mats. They wrote words of encouragement on the underside of each one, so every day, Dewone and Jade are surrounded by blessings—even in places they can’t see.</p><p>This project was truly special.Dewone’s story is one of resilience, love, and joy. We are proud to make his world safer, easier, and brighter.</p>",
  "quote": "\"Take care of what you pray for\" - Jade, Dewone's mother",
